{"lemma":"حُرَّةٍ","slug":"حُرَّةٍ","root":"ح.ر.ر","root_slug":"ح-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حُرّ","root":"حرر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7507","n7509"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"free"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unimpeded"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"set free, freedman"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"born free and noble"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"virtuous, genuine, true, pure, good"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unmixed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"heat"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"burning of the heart, from pain, wrath, distress, affliction, trouble or fatigue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"difficulty or severity of work"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vulva, pudendum of a woman"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħurr/","/ħarr/","/ħirr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7507","headword_ar":"حَرَّةٌ","root":"Hr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stony tract, of which the stones are black"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and worn and crumbling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though burned with fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hard and rugged tract of ground, strewn with black and worn and crumbling stones, as though they were rained down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a level tract abounding with stones, over which it is difficult to walk, and hard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereof the stones are"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black above and white beneath:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to AA,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a round form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as is oblong, not wide, is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuraAE","text_ar":"كُرَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~N","text_ar":"حَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or rather this is a coll. gen. n., (MF,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiraArN","text_ar":"حِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~aAtN","text_ar":"حَرَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~uwna","text_ar":"حَرُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araDuwna","text_ar":"اَرَضُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yoo, S,) to which it is made like because it is fem., as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is, (Yoo,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHar~uwna","text_ar":"اَحَرُّونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) as though the sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHar~apN","text_ar":"اَحَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yoo, Sb, S,) though this sing. is not used; (Yoo;) or as though its sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHar~u","text_ar":"اَحَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Th, who app. means that this place is hotter than others. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","IAar","MF","A","Yoo","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n7509","headword_ar":"حِرَّةٌ","root":"Hr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~N","text_ar":"حَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burning, in the throat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it increases, it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarowapN","text_ar":"حَرْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraArapN","text_ar":"حَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heat and burning of thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd:) it may be said that it is with kesr [instead of fet-h (see 1)] for the purpose of its being assimilated in form to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qir~apN","text_ar":"قِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which it occurs. (S, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAhu A@ll~`hu biAlHir~api taHota Alqir~api","text_ar":"رَمَاهُ ا@للّٰهُ بِالحِرَّةِ تَحْتَ القِرَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God afflict him by thirst with cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlHir~api","text_ar":"بِالحِرَّةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlqir~api","text_ar":"وَالقِرَّةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thirst and cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ad~u AlEaTa$i","text_ar":"اَشَدُّ العَطَشِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hir~apN EalaY qir~apK","text_ar":"حِرَّةٌ عَلَى قِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most severe of thirst is thirst in a cold day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hir~apN taHota qir~apK","text_ar":"حِرَّةٌ تَحْتَ قِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thirst in a cold day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd:) a prov., applied to him who makes a show of the contrary of that which he conceals; (TA;) or who makes a show of friendship while he conceals hatred. (Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","IDrd","K","ISd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}